// KNOWN-WRONG SCHEMA, kept as the evidence that produced the finding.
// The re-run (run 29633526704) proved the real cargo_pup top-level struct is
// `LintBuilder`, not `Pup` (error: "Expected struct LintBuilder but found Pup").
// It also showed these single-file crates present to pup as `unknown_crate`
// (the §3.5-documented caveat), so they are too structureless to hang a
// restrict_imports rule on. Closing the enforcement proof needs a richer
// fixture + a LintBuilder config — see PLAN.md P34 "Next Steps". Until then the
// stable `cargo metadata` gate (gate.py) is the proven §11 enforcement.
Pup(
    lints: [
        ArchitectureLint(
            name: "core-must-not-depend-on-ai",
            forbidden: [
                (from: "wcore", to: "wai"),
            ],
        ),
    ],
)
